book:
Alternative PHP Cache
APC


 &reftitle.intro;


  The Alternative PHP Cache (APC) is a free and open opcode cache for PHP.
  Its goal is to provide a free, open, and robust framework for
  caching and optimizing PHP intermediate code.



   &pecl.info.dead.git; &url.apc.source;.





   Alternatives to this extension are OPcache, APCu,
   Windows Cache for PHP and the Session Upload Progress API.




